1. Database configuration

Set($Actitime_DB_DSN, 'DBI:mysql:database=actitime;host=localhost;port=3306;mysql_enable_utf8=1');
Set($Actitime_DB_USER, 'actitime');
Set($Actitime_DB_PASS, 'actitime');

2. Webinterface
Set($Actitime_HTTP_URL, 'https://fqdn-ofmy-timesheet.local/actitime');

3. Misc options

Field name to query for ticket identification
Set($Actitime_PROJECT_NAME, 'p.name_lower');
Set($Actitime_CUSTOMER_NAME, 'c.name_lower');

Query part of the field (used sprintf to create the part)

1st argument is the ticketid
Set($Actitime_PROJECT_QUERY, '[netways #%d]: %%');
Set($Actitime_CUSTOMER_QUERY, '%%[%d]%%');

Name of the client customfield
Set($Actitime_CUSTOMER_FIELD_NAME, 'Client');

Default warning and critical ranges in percent (if budget is set)

Set($Actitime_BUDGET_WARNING_PERCENT, 60);
Set($Actitime_BUDGET_CRITICAL_PERCENT, 90);

If you want to include all other tasks not configured as groups

Set($Actitime_TASK_SHOW_ALL, 1);

Group configuration. You can combine multiple tasks into on view item

Set($Actitime_TASK_CONFIGURATION, [{
    'name'      => 'Group1',
    'active'    => ['my-task1', 'my-task2'],
    'inactive'  => ['my-not-billing'],

    'budget_warning_percent'    => 60,
    'budget_critical_percent'   => 90,
}]);
